results.name: Maximum divisor of n that is 1 or whose prime indices have a common divisor > 1.
comment: A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798. Numbers whose prime indices have a common divisor > 1 are listed in A318978, which is the union of this sequence without 1.
link: Gus Wiseman, Sequences counting and encoding certain classes of multisets
formula: n belongs to A318978 iff a(n) = 1.
example: The divisors of 90 that are 1 or whose prime indices have a common divisor > 1 are {1, 3, 5, 9}, so a(90) = 9.
xref: The union consists of {1} followed by A318978.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 21 2019
